  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **Facebook does not provide a feature that allows users to see who has viewed their profile**. If you come across any third-party apps or services claiming to offer this functionality, exercise caution for the following reasons:\n\n1. **Privacy Concerns**: These apps often require access to your Facebook account information, which can compromise your privacy and security.\n\n2. **Scams and Malware**: Many of these services are scams designed to collect your personal data or distribute malware.\n\n3. **Violation of Facebook\u2019s Policies**: Using third-party apps to access or display profile viewers can violate Facebook's terms of service, potentially leading to account restrictions or bans.\n\n### What You *Can* See on Facebook\n\nWhile you can't see who has viewed your profile, Facebook does offer other insights into how users are interacting with your content:\n\n- **Story Views**: If you post Stories on Facebook, you can see a list of users who have viewed each Story during the time it's active (typically 24 hours).\n\n- **Post Engagement**: You can view who has liked, commented on, or shared your posts, giving you an idea of who is engaging with your content.\n\n- **Profile Visits Through Mutual Interactions**: Sometimes, mutual friends or recent interactions can give indirect hints about who might be interested in your profile, but this is not a definitive way to see profile visitors.\n\n### Protecting Your Privacy\n\nIf you're concerned about your privacy on Facebook, consider the following tips:\n\n- **Review Privacy Settings**: Adjust your privacy settings to control who can see your posts, profile information, and contact you.\n\n- **Be Cautious with Third-Party Apps**: Avoid granting permissions to apps or services that request unnecessary access to your Facebook data.\n\n- **Stay Informed**: Regularly check Facebook\u2019s [Privacy Basics](https://www.facebook.com/help/325807937506242) to stay updated on how your information is used and how you can protect it.\n\n### Conclusion\n\nWhile the desire to know who\u2019s viewing your profile is understandable, Facebook prioritizes user privacy and doesn't offer this information. Always be wary of third-party solutions claiming to provide profile viewer data, as they often pose significant security risks.\n\nIf Facebook introduces new features related to profile views in the future, you can find official information and updates through their [Help Center](https://www.facebook.com/help/) or [Newsroom](https://about.meta.com/news/).",
